This paper discusses recent advances in distributed language models, which are commonly studied in the field of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of Bayes rule for classification, which is a common technique in machine learning and statistics, suggesting that it could also fit into the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of Yelp reviews as a dataset, which could suggest a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR) or computer vision (cs.CV) if the reviews include images.
